{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a8dac901-8acb-4f00-9325-bf45045bd38a","content":"TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively, so you filter with `--treenode-filter`. The pattern is `/<assembly>/<namespace>/<class>/<test>`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nThis matches `SmsNotificationTests` regardless of assembly or namespace. You can also be fully explicit:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/TestProject/Contoso.Notifications.Tests/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"299f444d-5855-48f3-8752-496fa04cf0e2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project (v0.6.120). TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) by default as its runner. For MTP-based runners, the filter syntax is different from VSTest.\n\nFor TUnit with MTP, you filter by class using the `--treenode-filter` option:\n\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nOr alternatively, TUnit also supports `--filter` with the MTP filter syntax. Let me think about this more carefully.\n\nActually, TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively. The filter syntax for MTP with TUnit uses `--treenode-filter` which follows the pattern `/<assembly>/<namespace>/<class>/<test>`.\n\n\nSo to run just the SmsNotificationTests class, I can use the wildcard pattern to match any assembly and namespace, or be more specific with the full path like `/TestProject/Contoso.Notifications.Tests/SmsNotificationTests`.","outputTokens":479,"requestId":"9838:3A3A20:20CBE4:2AF7BD:69FFDF95"},"id":"9b652c8c-80fd-49f7-93a6-c493351be03b","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:30:07.497Z","parentId":"c6f284fa-39da-4daa-a224-a095093fea45"}
